I must now discourse upon the Paraguay, from which the Parana receives its chief aug- mentation. The origin of this river has occa- sioned as great a dispute as that of the Parana It is, however, now established beyond all doubt, that those persons who have written that this river comes out of the lake Xarayes are quite mistaken.
